DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(1,5,1);
$a2 = $a1*$a1*$a1;
$d1 = random(.1,.4,.1);
$b1 = $a2+$d1;
$m1 = (1/3)*$a2**(-2/3);
$y1 = $a1;

BEGIN_TEXT

Use differential, (i.e. linear approximation), to approximate
\(  \sqrt[3] { $b1 } \) as follows: $BR$BR
Let \( f(x) = \sqrt[3] x \). The linear approximation to \( f(x) \) at \( x = $a2 \) can be written in the form \( y = mx+b \). Computer \(m\) and \(b\).
$BR$BR\( m =\) \{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
\( b =\) \{ans_rule(20) \} $BR
$BR$BR

Using this, find the approximation for \( \sqrt[3] {$b1} \).
$BR Answer: \{ans_rule(20) \}
END_TEXT

$ans1 = "$y1 -($m1*$a2)";
$ans2 = $m1*$b1 + $y1 -$m1*$a2;

ANS(num_cmp($m1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
